bib_record.title: Measurements of thermal neutron diffraction and inelastic scattering in reactor-grade graphite

free_txt: ADNA Corporation,Los Alamos,New Mexico
Measurements were conducted at the
Los Alamos Neutron Science Center pulsed neutron
facility at the Los Alamos National Laboratory.
Cross section of thermal neutron diffraction and
inelastic scattering depend on the structure
and manufacturing technology of the graphite sample.
In general, the inelastic scattering cross section of
reactor grade graphite is higher than cross section
of pyrolytic graphite with almost perfect crystaline
structure.
